{"id": 7178, "title": "Ticket #7178: new materialization is not triggered when jobs begin to run", "description": "<blockquote>\nWhen a job that is part of a late materialization cluster changes to run state, the cluster should materialize new jobs up to the max_idle limit.  This isn't happening unless the transaction that commits the change of state of the job also changes the cluster ad (which doesn't usually happen).\n\n<p>In practice, new jobs only materialize when existing jobs in that cluster are removed from the queue, because job removal (completion) will change the cluster ad.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2019-Aug-05 17:10:08 by jfrey:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>Code Review</strong>\n\n<p>This looks good.</p></blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-Aug-06 12:54</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/46bb74521fdbd0a5626e80d24fcb35333c2bde42\">[57607]</a></span>: version history for <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=7178\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7178'); return false;\" title=\"new materialization is not triggered when jobs begin to run\">#7178</a></span>  (By John (TJ) Knoeller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-Aug-02 16:27</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/2db0057c6b146719f7b181dda1b519624c4699a5\">[57566]</a></span>: fix job_late_materialize_py test for <span class=\"ticket\"><a class